post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

DPA Staff, Students, and Families,

Thank you for another amazing school year at Detroit Premier Academy! As I walked the halls today, I truly missed seeing all of you. Thank you for your support and understanding as we navigated through these last 12 weeks of remote learning. I hope everyone has a wonderful summer.

Stay safe and well!

Principal Bauer

Dear DPA Families,
>>>>>>> master

Detroit Premier Academy teachers have gone to extraordinary lengths to swiftly transition to supporting their students' learning at home. Teacher Appreciation Week is May 4-8, 2020. This is the perfect time for us to thank teachers for their tremendous dedication, creativity and problem solving during the pandemic.

DPA invites you to participate and give thanks to our deserving teachers! During this week, we invite everyone to share a post, picture or video thanking a teacher. Tell us how your child’s teacher has gone above and beyond to support your scholar during #COVID 19 or share something you learned from a teacher. We may not be able to hug our teachers right now, but we can still send them love virtually!

Sincerely,
The DPA Admin Team
text:
Dear DPA Families,

Detroit Premier Academy teachers have gone to extraordinary lengths to swiftly transition to supporting their students' learning at home. Teacher Appreciation Week is May 4-8, 2020. This is the perfect time for us to thank teachers for their tremendous dedication, creativity and problem solving during the pandemic.

DPA invites you to participate and give thanks to our deserving teachers! During this week, we invite everyone to share a post, picture or video thanking a teacher. Tell us how your child’s teacher has gone above and beyond to support your scholar during #COVID 19 or share something you learned from a teacher. We may not be able to hug our teachers right now, but we can still send them love virtually!

Sincerely,
The DPA Admin Team

We are thankful!

Communities In Schools of Michigan
April 2 at 10:46 AM ·

It's official, schools in Michigan are closed for the rest of the school year, per Governor Whitmer's Executive Order # 2020-35.

We've taken our work beyond the school walls. See how Communities In Schools of Michigan, Communities In Schools of Kalamazoo, and Communities In Schools of Northwest Michigan are doing whatever it takes for our students to succeed. We are #AllinforKids!

Connect with us about how you can help the students and families of Benton Harbor Area Schools, Battle Creek Public Schools, Dearborn Public Schools, Detroit Premier Academy, East English Village Preparatory Academy, Pontiac School District, Regent Park Scholars Charter Academy, Waverly Community Schools, and Ypsilanti Community Schools.

Video made by: Communities In Schools

#DoingMIPart #WhatWeAreMadeOf #COVID19

link:
DPA are so lucky to have YMV - Young Men of Vision this year.

It is the purpose of Young Men of Vision to mentor and teach under-served middle school students in Detroit, ages 12-14 to develop residual skills in various areas that build academic strength, self-confidence/awareness, and social intelligence.

Our young men have been having a great time. They've learned about the 7 steps of the decision making process. They work on and recite weekly affirmations, physical fitness and fitness competitions as well as team building.

Our young men were just gifted entire uniforms from the organization . Rob Johns of Building Futures has been an awesome mentor to our young men and we look forward to the many opportunities to come.
